Description of adult male. Total body length 1.09 mm ; paratypes 0.91–1.09 mm . Body (
Fig. 9
) elongate, heavily chitinised and perforated; 8.6 times as long as wide; thoracomeres and pleomeres telescoping into each other to varying degrees. In lateral view, pleomeres wider than thoracomeres. Head (
Fig. 9
) about as long as wide, 1.2 times as long as first 2 thoracomeres combined.
